      "review_summary": "The PR changes the Amazon Bedrock plugin runtime and tests so direct `amazon.nova-*` models skip the no-cache wrapper and receive Bedrock Converse cache points via `onPayload`.\n\nPR surface: Source +26, Tests 0. Total +26 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level. Current main forces direct Nova through the no-cache path, while PR head only recognizes the direct `amazon.nova-` prefix and injects `short` cache points regardless of explicit retention semantics.",
